@Emmanuel this must be an older argument where the other side has deleted their comments. I believe the statement is incomplete and the argument one of semantics and unhelpful for anyone. 

The word free depends upon it's context in order to determine the interpretation of cost. Such as sodium-free, or free from US currency on the part of the person obtaining the instructional material. 

So your argument is really one of semantics, which could also be interpreted as someone looking for an argument to an incomplete statement. In my experience this can be considered bad netiquette. I suggest you remove your comment as will I, for respect of Dr. Severance and his hard work and incredibly generous offerings 😊.
